Title: Derivative Expansion in Quantum Theory of Gravitation

Authors: K.-I. Izawa

Comments: phyzzx, 8 pages, UT-686

Journal-ref: Prog.Theor.Phys. 93 (1995) 615-620

The cosmological term prevents perturbation based on derivative expansion inEinstein gravity. We consider quantum theory of gravitation invariant undervolume-preserving diffeomorphism and Weyl transformation, which is suitable forderivative expansion.